In practice, imaging with EIT during either an expiratory pause or an inspiratory pause may allow more information on lung recruitment to be obtained, and it would be anticipated that one key use of EIT would be to allow visualization during the process of formal lung recruitment to see whether additional pressures actually can open up closed airways and whether additional PEEP can keep these airways open. This is potentially valuable as current methods such as compliance assessment or changes in \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
